{
  "data": [
    {
      "id": 993,
      "documentId": "wmxaunywn3rwih6ac8ug1tg2",
      "Title": "GAIL to Invest ₹3,800 Cr in Solar Projects with Storage in UP, Maharashtra",
      "slug": "gail-to-invest-3-800-cr-in-solar-projects-with-storage-in-up-maharashtra",
      "Excerpt": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "GAIL will invest ₹3,800 crore to set up 700 MW solar capacity with storage, boosting renewable portfolio and ensuring round-the-clock power for key petrochemical units.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "Content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "As a part of its push towards clean energy and Net Zero goals, Maharatna public sector unit GAIL (India) Ltd will invest ₹3,800 crore to set up 700 MW of solar power capacity across Uttar Pradesh and Maharashtra, reports PTI.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "The company said on Tuesday that it will develop a 600-MW solar project with a 550-MWh battery energy storage system at the TUSCO Solar Park in Uttar Pradesh’s Jhansi. This is to primarily meet the captive power needs of its petrochemical plant at Pata in the state. Besides, it will set up a 100-MW solar project with a 22-MWh storage system in Maharashtra’s Sambhaji Nagar to cater to its PDH-PP plant in Raigad.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "According to the company, the projects are aimed at boosting renewable energy capacity and ensuring 24x7 power supply through integrated storage solutions. After commissioning, GAIL's installed renewable energy capacity is expected to increase to over 1,000 MW from 147 MW.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "“GAIL's installed renewable energy capacity shall increase substantially to over 1,000 MW from the current 147 MW upon commissioning of these projects,” said Deepak Gupta, Chairman and Managing Director, GAIL. This expansion underscores the company’s strategic vision to align its growth trajectory with environmental responsibility while ensuring long-term energy security, he added.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
